<title>REPUBLIC OF IRELAND: Arcon says to create 125 jobs at Galmoy mine.</title>
<headline>Arcon says to create 125 jobs at Galmoy mine.</headline>
<dateline>DUBLIN 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ireland's exploration and mining firm Arcon on Monday announced that it is to create 125 new jobs as part of the final preparation for full production at its lead and zinc mine at Galmoy in County Kilkenny.</p>
<p>The company said in a statement the majority of the new positions will be recruited locally from the surrounding counties of Kilkenny, Laois and Tipperary.</p>
<p>Arcon said the recruitment programmed marked the fulfilment of a commitment which the company had made when it first began work on the Galmoy project.</p>
<p>The company said it was currently on schedule to commence production at the beginning of 1997 and the on-site workforce will eventually increase to 200.</p>
<p>-- Dublin Newsroom +353 1 6603377</p>
